  {
    "title": "Lore",
    "depth": 1,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Lesley grew up in the Vance household, where her father presided over the noble family's security."
          },
          {
            "text": "During an unexpected attack by a rival family, Lesley's father was killed."
          },
          {
            "text": "As the assailants approached the Vance household, Lesley took up her father's black long rifle and fulfilled her late father's mission."
          },
          {
            "text": "Tears rolled down Lesley's cheeks as she fired shot after shot, surprisingly, each one taking down an assassin."
          },
          {
            "text": "The final tear came as the final shot took down the last of the rival family's men."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Lesley was adopted by the Vance family, with the patriarch of the noble house even putting their sole heir, Harley under her tutelage."
          },
          {
            "text": "Harley, was a natural troublemaker, who used his talents in magic to unintentionally cause trouble for the Vance household."
          },
          {
            "text": "Only Lesley could keep Harley under control."
          },
          {
            "text": "Harley's troublemaking streak was the last part of warmth within Lesley's conscience."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "After hearing about how Harley had travelled to the dangerous Land of Dawn after defeating the Boss of Dark Magic, Lesley followed him, along with her trusty heirloom rifle.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Land of Dawn"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "After she found Harley through a long arduous journey, she discovered that the once immature young boy [has] changed through the numerous life experiences he had gone through."
          },
          {
            "text": "She decided it would be best to have her adopted little brother train, alone, while she would silently protect him from within the shadows."
          },
          {
            "text": "From that day on, all the monsters that were inflicted with Harley's magic would also be struck with a black bullet, that would impeccably pierce through their heart."
          },
          {
            "text": "The stories of the magical youngster who was followed by a mysterious black sniper, soon spread across the Land of Dawn, like wild fire."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "templates": [
      {
        "template": "clr"
      }
    ]
