    "lists": [
      [
        {
          "text": "The name Lesley has Scottish origins and means \"garden of holly\" or \"fortress of holly\". It comes from the Scottish surname Leslie, which was derived from a place name in Scotland. Her name might symbolize her precision, stealth, and resilience, much like a fortress that stands strong or a sharpshooter hiding in the shadows.",
          "formatting": {
            "bold": [
              "Lesley",
              "\"garden of holly\"",
              "\"fortress of holly\"",
              "precision, stealth, and resilience"
            ],
            "italic": [
              "Leslie"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "Unlike other Marksmen, Lesley doesn’t rely on attack speed, she focuses on high burst damage from critical hits."
        },
        {
          "text": "Lesley is one of the few marksmen in the game who use Energy instead of Mana."
        },
        {
          "text": "Her passive, Lethal Shot, allows her to deal 100% critical damage after gaining extra energy, making her a sniper-type hero rather than a typical ADC (Attack Damage Carry).",
          "formatting": {
            "bold": [
              "Lethal Shot"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "Both Lesley and 's royal house \"Vance\" means \"Marsh, Mud, and Fen\" in Old English which is used as a masculine given name and surname mostly of American usage"
        },
        {
          "text": "Lesley's Quote; \"Enemy in range, and you are too.\" is a reference from Murphy's Law of Combat.",
          "formatting": {
            "italic": [
              "\"Enemy in range, and you are too.\""
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "Lesley is the first and, so far, the only Marksman/Assassin hero in the game, whereas is an Assassin/Marksman.",
          "links": [
            {
              "text": "Marksman/",
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Marksman"
            },
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Assassin"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "In her early designs, she had shorter hair and a more military-style outfit. The developers later gave her a long coat and a more assassin-like appearance, making her more stylish and deadly."
        }
      ]
    ]
  }
